article_title: Schock visits with Whalen on route in 18th district
article_text:
By Patrick Stout

pstout@McDonoughVoice.com

Posted Feb. 14, 2014 at 12:01 AM

Updated Feb 14, 2014 at 11:05 PM

MACOMB —

article_metadata.description: U.S. Rep. Aaron Schock, R-Peoria, visited manufacturing plants in Macomb and Quincy on Thursday as part of his latest round of visits throughout his 18th Congressional District.Schock said he would be back in Washington, D.C. next Tuesday.The congressman visited Knapheide in Quincy and Whalen Manufacturing in Macomb.
